====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# The movement of something that creeps (like worms or snails)
# A relatively small gradual change, variation or deviation (from a planned value) in a measure.
# A slight displacement of an object: the slight movement of something
# The gradual expansion or proliferation of something beyond its original goals or boundaries, considered negatively.
#: ''Christmas '''creep'''. Feature '''creep'''. Instruction '''creep'''. Mission '''creep'''
# {{lb|en|publishing}} In sewn books, the tendency of [[page]]s on the inside of a [[quire]] to stand out farther than those on the outside of it.
# {{lb|en|materials science}} An increase in [[strain]] with time; the gradual [[flow]] or [[deformation]] of a material under [[stress]].
# {{lb|en|geology}} The [[imperceptible]] [[downslope]] movement of surface [[rock]].
# {{lb|en|informal|pejorative}} someone unpleasantly strange or eccentric
# {{lb|en|informal|pejorative}} A frightening and/or disconcerting person, especially one who gives the speaker [[chills]] or who induces [[psychosomatic]] facial itching.
#: ''Stop following me, you '''creep'''!''
# {{lb|en|agriculture}} A barrier with small openings used to keep large animals out while allowing smaller animals to pass through.

